# Legacy Files Are Reference Material

- Existing files in this repository are source material for the rebuild, not the final package design.
- Preserve validated statistical intent and domain logic, but do not preserve legacy naming, file layout, comments, or ad hoc structure by default.
- Do not copy old files verbatim into the formal package unless explicitly requested.
- Freely reorganize code into better package modules, as long as behavior is preserved or migration notes are provided.
- When reusing legacy code, first identify what is core logic versus what is temporary, exploratory, or redundant.
- If there is a conflict between legacy layout and standard package practice, prefer standard package practice.
